RAPPER Big Xhosa has expressed his love for actress Thembi Seete. The musician, whose real name is Sesethu Myeki, poured his heart out to her on Instagram on Tuesday, 12 July. Big Xhosa (24), known for his controversial songs including iTlof Tlof, shared how much he loved Thembi. He made a lyrical love letter to the telenovela Gomora actress about how much he adored her. ALSO READ : Oskido’s son is a graduate! “Hi Thembi, I was wondering if you have an extra heart because you just stole mine. You must be a parking ticket because you got fine written all over you, love. Damn, undiphadile,” he wrote. Big Xhosa said though he should have kept these words inside, he could not do so as his love for Thembi was like a diarrhoea. “And lastly, if I could rearrange the alphabets, I would put “U” and “I” together,” he added. The caption left many of his followers in stitches, with Zoyasa saying he tried his luck well. Then Goitsimang Setshogoe laughed out loud, advising him to make a song about Thembi. Scott Regards wrote: “I hope she replies.” A post shared by BIG XHOSA (@bigxhosa_) 